description:
This is a clip from an unreleased instructional documentary I did a number of years ago...
In it, I interviewed three of the top specialists in the funky and swinging organ combo groove sound, Royce Campbell, Rudy Petschauer and Jerry Weldon.  (Rudy and Jerry were key members of Jack McDuff's heating station for over 10 years... and in my book, no one alive today swings or can play better boogaloo than Rudy - - well, almost no one...)  - - We had just done a session together and I decided to use it as an opportunity to go on a quest to find out the true meaning of "groove" and "swing" and musicians of their caliber get the feel and what it means.   They also shared some of their memories playing with some of the greats and what they learned from them.

Here, Rudy talks about "booglaoo" vs. "funk" style drumming and also demonstrates a swinging uptown style "conga" beat.  

This video was recorded on the same day I did "Get Wicked" - - the drum beat from which can be heard on that video of mine that so many people seem to have dug hear on YOU TUBE.

The video was shot at MAJA STUDIO in my hometown of Philadelphia.  There's also a sequence where the engineer takes you  on a tour of the studio and we talk about how to mic and record a Leslie.  Will try to get it up (sooner or later !)

Enjoy !
title: Boogaloo, Funky and Swinging JAZZ Organ combo drumming (instruction)
